<item>
            <title>[SEC-896] Authentication tag throws NPE if custom principal property evaluates to null</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-896</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Stacktrace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.springframework.security.taglibs.authz.AuthenticationTag.doEndTag(AuthenticationTag.java:123)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caused by the following JSP code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;s:authentication property=&quot;principal.customProperty&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where the custom UserDetails property &quot;customProperty&quot; is set to null. To fix, change line org/springframework/security/taglibs/authz/AuthenticationTag.java:123 from &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            writeMessage(result.toString());  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            writeMessage(String.valueOf(result));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in order to avoid NPE where a property returns null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
